  <h1>TokenFire Privacy Policy</h1>
  <br>
  <p>
    <b class="text-error">We are currently in alpha testing so changes may happen frequently. Please be aware.</b>
  </p>
  <br>
  <p>
    We at TokenFire, Inc. (“TokenFire,” “we,” “us,” “our,”) know that our users (“you,” “your”) care about how your personal information is used and shared, and we take your privacy seriously. Please read the following Privacy Policy (the “Privacy Policy”) to learn about how we use your personal information. By visiting, accessing or using the www.tokenfire.com website or application, and any other linked pages, features, content, or any other services we offer from time to time in connection therewith (collectively, “TokenFire Platform"), you acknowledge that you accept the practices and policies outlined in this Privacy Policy, and you hereby consent that we will collect, use, and share your information in the following ways. This Privacy Policy only applies to products and services related to TokenFire; other products and services provided by TokenFire may be governed by separate privacy policies.
  </p>
  <br>
  <h3>
    I. What does this Privacy Policy cover?
  </h3>
  <br>
  <p>
    This Privacy Policy covers TokenFire’s treatment of personally identifiable information (“Personal Information”) that we gather when you use or access TokenFire and/or any TokenFire products and services. This policy does not apply to the practices of companies that we do not own or control, or to individuals we do not employ or manage.
  </p>
  <p>
    TokenFire does not knowingly collect or solicit Personal Information from anyone under the age of 13 or knowingly allow such persons to register. If you are under 13, please do not attempt to register for TokenFire or send any information about yourself to us, including your name, address, telephone number, or email address. No one under age 13 may provide any Personal Information to TokenFire or through TokenFire. In the event that we learn that we have collected Personal Information from a child under age 13 without verification of parental consent, we will delete that information as quickly as possible. If you believe that we might have any information from or about a child under 13, please contact us at <a href="mailto:privacy@tokenfire.com">privacy@tokenfire.com</a>.
  </p>
  <br>
  <h3>
    II. What Information Does TokenFire Collect?
  </h3>
  <br>
  <p>
    We gather various types of Personal Information from our users and may use this Personal Information to personalize and improve our services, to allow our users to set up a user account and profile, to contact users, to fulfill your requests for certain products and services, to analyze how users interact with TokenFire, and as otherwise said in this Privacy Policy. We may share certain types of Personal Information with third parties (as set forth in this Section and in Section III).
  </p>
  <br>
  <h4>
    Personal Information You Provide to Us
  </h4>
  <ol type="A">
    <li>
      <b>General Information.</b> We receive and store information you knowingly provide to us. For example, during the registration process, we collect Personal Information such as your username, e-mail address, gender, and age. We may collect other Personal Information you provide us through your use of our services. For example, if you respond to surveys or otherwise interact with TokenFire. You can choose not to provide us with certain information, but you may not be able to take advantage of many of our special features. The Personal Information you provide us is used for such purpose as answering questions, improving the content and quality of our services, and customizing content you see, and communicating with you about TokenFire’s products and services.
    </li>
    <li>
      <b>Customer Support.</b> If you contact us regarding a problem with our services or submit feedback, suggestions, complaints, questions, or any other e-mail correspondence, TokenFire asks for contact information that may include your e-mail address or other Personal Information so we may respond to your inquiries. This information will be used to notify you of receipt of your submission and resolution to the inquiry. We may use this information to also contact you in order to conduct surveys to improve our customer support and other TokenFire services. We may employ a third party service provider to conduct such surveys and customer support related responses on our behalf. The third party will be prohibited from using your Personal Information for any other purposes.
    </li>
  </ol>
  <br>
  <h4>
    Personal Information Collected Automatically
  </h4>
  <ol type="A">
    <li>
      <b>Browser Information.</b> While using the TokenFire services, we will collect information about your browser, which may include IP address, browser type, cookie information, timestamps, operating system, and requested pages.
    </li>
    <li>
      <b>Device Information.</b> Information about your device such as manufacturer, operating system, and screen size may be collected from using TokenFire. This information will be used to improve the quality of our services.
    </li>
    <li>
      <b>Device ID.</b> During the installation of TokenFire on your mobile device, we will gather information about your device including type and ID (including any identifier, regardless of issuing source, that operates to uniquely identify your device which may include, but not limited, to Android ID and MAC address) (“Device ID”). By installing and using TokenFire, you are providing us consent to use such Device IDs in connection with the services you’ve requested. We use your Device ID information, with other provided or collected information, to provide you with certain features, such as tracking virtual achievements, tracking reward redemptions, and organizing TokenFire-related applications.
    </li>
    <li>
      <b>Usage.</b> Our service collects usage information, such as the amounts, frequency, and duration of users accessing and using TokenFire and its services including reward, gameplay, app, and website-related usage.  This information enables us to understand how our users use our services so that we can improve our services and provide better content. As part of this use of information, we may provide aggregate information to our partners about how users use our services. We share this aggregate information so they may also improve their services and content. TokenFire only provides partners aggregate information so that they would be unable to identify you personally.
    </li>
  </ol>
  <br>
  <h4>
    E-mail and Other Communications
  </h4>
  <p>
    We may contact you, by e-mail or other means about updates to our services or TokenFire-related apps. Rewards will also be delivered via e-mail. If you do not want to receive e-mail or other communication from us, please message us at <a href="mailto:privacy@tokenfire.com">privacy@tokenfire.com</a>. Also, we may receive a confirmation when you an email from us if your computer or device supports this functionality. This confirmation helps us make emails more interesting and helpful and to improve our services.
  </p>
  <br>
  <h4>
    What About Cookies?
  </h4>
  <p>
    Cookies are identifiers that we transfer to your computer (or other device) through your browser to allow us to recognize your browser and tell us how and when pages in our site are visited and by how many people. We use cookies to enhance visitors’ experiences, to learn more about their use of our services and to improve quality and content. You can find more information on cookies and how to manage them at www.allaboutcookies.org.
  </p>
  <p>
    Most browsers have an option for turning off the cookie feature, which will prevent your browser from accepting new cookies, as well as (depending on the sophistication of your browser software) allowing you to decide on acceptance of each new cookie in a variety of ways. We strongly recommend that you leave the cookies activated, however, because cookies enable you to take advantage of some of our TokenFire’s most attractive features.
  </p>
  <p>
    Our advertising partners, who may set cookies, may deliver ads to users. These cookies allow the ad server to recognize your computer or other device each time they send you an online advertisement to compile information about you or others who use your computer or device. This information allows ad networks to, among other things, deliver targeted advertisements that they believe will be of most interest to you. This Privacy Policy covers the use of cookies by TokenFire and does not cover the use of cookies by any advertisers.
  </p>
  <br>
  <h3>
    III. Will TokenFire Share Any of the Information It Receives?
  </h3>
  <br>
  <p>
    We neither rent nor sell your Personal Information to anyone. We share your Personal Information with third parties only as described in this Privacy Policy.
  </p>
  <ol type="A">
    <li>
      <b>Agents; Service Providers.</b> We employ other companies and people to perform tasks on our behalf and need to share your information with them to provide products or services to you. For example, we might use a statistical data service to help us improve TokenFire’s services. Unless we tell you differently, our agents do not have any right to use the Personal Information we share with them beyond what is necessary to assist us.
    </li>
    <li>
      <b>Advertisers.</b> TokenFire may allow advertisers to target users by demographic information to serve advertisements and you agree that we may use any of the information we have collected from you to select or allow advertisers to select the appropriate audience for those advertisements. For example, we may allow an advertiser to feature certain rewards based on your reward history.
    </li>
    <li>
      <b>Affiliated Businesses We Do Not Control.</b> In the future, we may become affiliated with a variety of businesses and work closely with them. In certain situations, these businesses may provide rewards to you through TokenFire or we may provide these services, products, and/or rewards jointly with the affiliated businesses. We will share your Personal Information that is related to such transactions with the affiliated business for the purposes of delivering the product and/or improving the content from affiliated businesses.
    </li>
    <li>
      <b>User Actions.</b> You understand that we cannot control what other users do with any content (including, without limitation, profile, images, ratings, captions, and comments) you voluntarily disclose for such users to view on TokenFire (“User Submissions”). Other users make your User Submissions publicly available to be collected and used by others, or to be redistributed through the Internet and other media channels. Users’ e-mail addresses will not be directly revealed to other users, except, when the user is “connected” to another user via shared group membership, or an invitation, or if the user has chosen to include their e-mail address in their public user profile.
    </li>
    <li>
      <b>Business Transfers.</b> In the event of a merger, acquisition, reorganization, change of control, sale of all or substantially all of its assets, or the sale of an individual mobile or web properties owned by us, customer information is typically one of the business assets that is transferred and we may therefore transfer and/or disclose your Personal Information to the prospective seller or buyer of such business or assets or to a third party as a part of such merger, acquisition, reorganization, or sale. In addition, if we go out of business or enter bankruptcy, Personal Information would be one of the assets transferred to or acquired by a third party.
    </li>
    <li>
      <b>Protection of TokenFire and Others.</b> We may release Personal Information when we believe in good faith that release is necessary to comply with the law; enforce or apply our conditions of use and other agreements; or protect the rights, property, or safety of TokenFire, our employees, our users, or others. This includes exchanging information with other companies and organizations for fraud protection and credit risk reduction.
    </li>
    <li>
      <b>With Your Consent.</b> Except as set forth above, you will be notified when your Personal Information may be shared with third parties, and will be able to prevent the sharing of this information.
    </li>
  </ol>
  <br>
  <h3>
    IV. Is Personal Information About me Secure?
  </h3>
  <br>
  <p>
    Your account is protected by a password for your privacy and security. You need to ensure that there is no unauthorized access to your account and Personal Information by selecting and protecting your password appropriately and limiting access to your computer or device by signing off after you have finished accessing your account.
  </p>
  <p>
    We endeavor to protect the privacy of your account and other Personal Information we hold in our records, but we cannot guarantee the security of user information. Unauthorized entry or use, hardware or software failure, and other factors, may compromise the security of user information at any time.
  </p>
  <p>
    TokenFire may contain links to other sites. We are not responsible for the privacy policies and/or practices of other sites. This Privacy Policy only governs information collected on TokenFire. When following a link to another site you should read that site’s privacy policy.
  </p>
  <br>
  <h3>
    V. What Personal Information Can I Access?
  </h3>
  <br>
  <p>
    Through your account settings, you may access and, in some cases, change or delete the following information you’ve provided to us.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Username and password</li>
    <li>E-mail Address</li>
    <li>User profile information</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    The information you can view and update through your account may change as TokenFire changes. If you have any questions about viewing or updating information we have on file about you, please contact us at <a href="mailto:privacy@tokenfire.com">privacy@tokenfire.com</a>.
  </p>
  <br>
  <h3>VI. What Choices Do I Have?</h3>
  <br>
  <p>
    You can always opt not to disclose information to us, though it may be necessary to take advantage of or register for certain features we provide.
  </p>
  <p>
    You are able to access, and in some cases, change or delete your information such as those listed in Section V. Some of the information may remain in our records after updating or deletion.
  </p>
  <p>
    You may request deletion of your account by sending us a message at <a href="mailto:privacy@tokenfire.com">privacy@tokenfire.com</a>. Again, some information may remain in our records after deletion of your account. This data may be used for aggregated data even after deletion, but not in a manner that would identify you personally.
  </p>
  <p>
    If you do not wish to receive communications from us, message us at <a href="mailto:privacy@tokenfire.com">privacy@tokenfire.com</a> or change your account settings. Please note that if you do not want to receive legal notices from us, such as this Privacy Policy, those legal notices will still govern your use of TokenFire, and you are responsible for reviewing such legal notices for change.
  </p>
  <br>
  <h3>
    VII. Changes to This Privacy Policy
  </h3>
  <br>
  <p>
    We may amend this Privacy Policy from time to time. Use of information we collect is subject to the Privacy Policy in effect at the time such information is used. If we make changes in the way we use Personal Information, we will post the changes on the TokenFire website or send you an email prior to the change becoming effective. Users are bound by any changes to the Privacy Policy when he or she uses the TokenFire Platform after such changes have been first posted.
  </p>
  <br>
  <h3>
    VIII. Questions or Concerns
  </h3>
  <br>
  <p>
    If you have any questions or concerns regarding our Privacy Policy, please send a message to <a href="mailto:privacy@tokenfire.com">privacy@tokenfire.com</a>. We will make every effort to resolve your concerns.
